WEBVTT

00:14.973 --> 00:16.182
[♪♪♪]

00:39.039 --> 00:40.540
[SNAKE RATTLING]

01:33.343 --> 01:34.552
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

01:41.017 --> 01:42.685
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

01:50.693 --> 01:52.237
[LINE RINGING]

01:52.320 --> 01:53.822
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

02:02.247 --> 02:03.915
Jimmy?

02:06.584 --> 02:07.502
<i>Yeah.</i>

02:08.795 --> 02:09.796
<i>It's me.</i>

02:09.879 --> 02:11.172
[SOBS]

02:14.425 --> 02:16.261
I'm okay.

02:16.344 --> 02:17.595
[KIM LAUGHING]

02:19.222 --> 02:20.598
[CRYING]

02:28.064 --> 02:29.149
[♪♪♪]

04:13.461 --> 04:14.462
TYRUS:
<i>You sure?</i>

04:15.463 --> 04:18.424
All right. Stay put, call me if there's a problem.

04:19.634 --> 04:23.805
Doesn't look like anyone's been down that road.
Definitely no one official.

04:23.888 --> 04:26.057
Bodies, trucks, it's all still there.

04:26.140 --> 04:30.019
A couple of flatbeds headed their way.
They'll clear it all out.

04:30.103 --> 04:32.480
Like it never happened.

04:32.563 --> 04:34.190
TYRUS:
And the one who followed you?

04:34.274 --> 04:37.485
We'll be damn lucky if we ever find that guy.

04:37.568 --> 04:41.114
Well, that'll have to do.
He's in the middle of nowhere.

04:42.282 --> 04:45.118
Don't go to sleep yet.

04:45.201 --> 04:47.704
We gotta work on your story.

04:49.247 --> 04:52.041
All right. Let's do it.

05:04.387 --> 05:07.265
De Guzman. Jorge.

05:23.614 --> 05:26.993
-Seven million dollars?
-Yep.

05:37.337 --> 05:38.546
[SAUL BREATHING HEAVILY]

05:54.437 --> 05:55.730
I'm fine.

05:56.773 --> 05:58.900
Seven million.

05:59.901 --> 06:04.113
Your client has $7 million.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.698
Where'd it come from?

06:06.949 --> 06:10.369
It's not for me to ask
where a client gets his money.

06:12.246 --> 06:15.083
And just who exactly is your client?

06:16.709 --> 06:19.921
Jorge De Guzman.

06:42.652 --> 06:43.486
Yes, hello?

06:46.447 --> 06:48.449
This is extra.

06:55.039 --> 06:58.084
And now, Mr. De Guzman?

07:12.890 --> 07:17.019
Well. You must have a story.

07:18.020 --> 07:19.480
Car trouble. Yeah.

07:19.564 --> 07:23.651
Broke down about six miles from the pick-up site.

07:23.734 --> 07:26.737
You know there's no cell reception
out there, right?

07:28.197 --> 07:29.657
Car trouble.

07:29.740 --> 07:32.201
Yeah. Just kaput.

07:34.328 --> 07:35.746
So, um...

07:36.747 --> 07:39.917
Why so long?
It's not that far back to the main road.

07:40.001 --> 07:41.836
You didn't just hitchhike?

07:41.919 --> 07:44.672
I thought of that. But you know, 7 mil in cash,

07:44.755 --> 07:47.467
I was kind of afraid who might pick me up.

07:47.550 --> 07:49.427
I didn't think it was worth the risk.

07:50.428 --> 07:51.596
I walked north.

07:51.679 --> 07:58.519
Probably not the smartest move,
but after a night lost in the desert, I made it.

08:01.772 --> 08:05.401
Well, that was the right call.

08:05.485 --> 08:08.196
Hey. Hey. You did good, huh?

08:08.279 --> 08:09.322
[GROANS]

08:10.615 --> 08:14.452
Anyway, listen, I wouldn't be too happy.

08:14.535 --> 08:18.289
Seven mil, it really sent up a huge flare.

08:18.372 --> 08:20.082
They're looking into you.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.960
I don't know how long "Jorge De Guzman"
is gonna hold up.

08:23.044 --> 08:26.380
Hey, listen, by the time
these dipshits figure it out,

08:26.464 --> 08:29.675
I will be long gone, man.

08:30.676 --> 08:32.637
Back home in Mexico, you know?

08:34.055 --> 08:35.306
Yeah.

08:35.389 --> 08:39.477
Hey! Hey, hey. But don't worry.
You and me? We're not done.

08:39.560 --> 08:42.647
We're gonna do things. Big things.

08:43.689 --> 08:45.608
Friend of the cartel, right?

08:46.359 --> 08:48.152
-Right.
-Right.

08:48.236 --> 08:50.112
[CAR APPROACHING]

08:54.825 --> 08:58.454
So hey, my cousins. They pay you?

08:59.455 --> 09:01.040
Yep.

09:01.123 --> 09:02.625
Perfecto.

09:02.708 --> 09:06.379
So make sure you buy something nice for the wife.
Man, she's a looker, huh?

09:07.630 --> 09:09.090
My-- My what?

09:09.173 --> 09:12.009
Yeah! She came by to see me.

09:12.093 --> 09:14.887
Hey, nice job, eh?

09:14.971 --> 09:18.057
I mean, for somebody who marries that far up...

09:19.058 --> 09:21.018
<i>Bien hecho, </i>man.

09:21.102 --> 09:23.104
Respect, you know?

09:31.279 --> 09:32.446
[WATER RUNNING]

09:33.823 --> 09:35.491
KIM:
Let me help.

09:38.369 --> 09:39.912
There.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.163
[GROANING]

09:44.333 --> 09:47.587
Oh, my God, Jimmy.
You need to go to an emergency room.

09:47.670 --> 09:51.841
I'm okay. I'm okay.
I cleaned it out real good at the truck stop.

09:51.924 --> 09:55.386
All right. Well, let's at least just go get you
an IV, huh? You're dehydrated.

09:55.469 --> 09:59.807
No. I don't need an IV.
I've been pounding sports drinks nonstop.

09:59.890 --> 10:03.519
-I'm really okay.
-All right.

10:03.603 --> 10:06.856
Come on, you're gonna get in this bath, though,
it'll help your skin.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.279
What is this? Cream of Wheat?

10:13.362 --> 10:16.282
Oatmeal. It's an oatmeal bath. Anti-inflammatory.

10:17.283 --> 10:19.243
It'll help your sunburn.

10:21.871 --> 10:22.955
[GROANING]

10:26.500 --> 10:29.629
-Is the temp okay?
-Yeah. It's good.

10:30.630 --> 10:31.672
You sure?

10:32.673 --> 10:33.841
Yeah.

10:34.842 --> 10:38.304
Okay. You don't want any food
or anything else to drink?

10:38.387 --> 10:39.930
No, I'm good.

10:40.014 --> 10:43.684
I just need to sit. This is good.

10:59.408 --> 11:03.037
I can't believe you walked
through the desert alone for 36 hours.

11:03.120 --> 11:05.956
I-- I can't even fathom it.

11:06.957 --> 11:08.584
That's right.

11:10.378 --> 11:12.213
All by myself.

11:19.845 --> 11:21.138
So...

11:23.432 --> 11:25.810
Is there anything you wanna tell me?

11:28.396 --> 11:30.064
-About?
-Lalo.

11:31.065 --> 11:32.817
You saw Lalo?

11:35.319 --> 11:36.821
Yeah.

11:37.905 --> 11:42.243
Jimmy, short of going to the police,
Lalo was the only lead I had to figure out--

11:42.326 --> 11:45.621
Kim, you have to stay away from people like Lalo.

11:47.039 --> 11:48.874
-Jimmy...
-You don't see Lalo.

11:48.958 --> 11:50.918
I see Lalo, okay?

11:51.001 --> 11:54.213
-I'm in the game. You're not in the game.
-What?

11:54.296 --> 11:56.006
The game?

11:57.007 --> 11:58.968
Listen, it was perfectly safe.

11:59.051 --> 12:02.847
I was at the MDC, surrounded by guards,
like any lawyer visiting a client, okay?

12:02.930 --> 12:04.390
But he's not your client.

12:04.473 --> 12:07.643
He's my client. So please, just keep away.

12:07.726 --> 12:10.896
Jimmy, I was worried about you.

12:10.980 --> 12:13.190
And I'm worried about you.

12:14.233 --> 12:16.235
Kim, when I was out there...

12:17.611 --> 12:20.239
I didn't think I was gonna make it.

12:20.322 --> 12:24.160
I thought I was done.

12:25.703 --> 12:28.539
I was that close to giving up.

12:29.748 --> 12:32.418
And the only thing that kept me going...

12:34.211 --> 12:36.589
was knowing that you were here.

12:38.174 --> 12:39.717
So...

12:41.802 --> 12:42.970
Okay.

12:44.221 --> 12:46.474
I won't see Lalo again.

12:47.892 --> 12:49.477
Good.

12:51.228 --> 12:52.646
Good.

13:19.048 --> 13:21.050
After all this...

13:22.843 --> 13:24.678
was it worth it?

13:30.059 --> 13:32.061
Go look in the bag.

13:34.271 --> 13:36.941
The bag in the living room.

13:42.321 --> 13:43.697
It's on the chair.

13:43.781 --> 13:45.950
It's a gray bag.

13:55.834 --> 13:57.086
[♪♪♪]

14:18.941 --> 14:20.192
You see it?

14:22.611 --> 14:24.405
Yeah, Jimmy.

14:25.865 --> 14:27.199
I see it.

14:29.827 --> 14:31.954
That's what it's all about.

14:49.513 --> 14:53.517
MIKE:
Six guys, three vehicles, heavily armed.

14:53.601 --> 14:57.771
My guess is they followed the Salamanca cousins
up from Chihuahua,

14:57.855 --> 15:01.400
trailing the money
but not wanting to take these two guys on.

15:01.483 --> 15:05.321
Now, I'm no expert, but they had tattoos.

15:05.404 --> 15:07.948
Same symbol I saw on a job back east.

15:08.032 --> 15:09.992
A Colombian gang.

15:10.993 --> 15:12.912
Draw it for me.

15:40.147 --> 15:41.982
These men were hired.

15:43.025 --> 15:44.610
By who?

15:46.570 --> 15:48.405
[GOLF SIMULATOR BEEPING]

15:50.199 --> 15:52.076
[CROWD CHEERING ON GOLF SIMULATOR]

15:55.412 --> 15:56.789
[CROWD GASPS ON GOLF SIMULATOR]

15:56.872 --> 15:58.332
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

16:04.088 --> 16:05.381
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:05.464 --> 16:07.466
GUS [OVER PHONE]:
<i>I trust you heard the good news.</i>

16:07.549 --> 16:10.052
Gustavo, which good news is that?

16:10.135 --> 16:14.556
Our colleague has been released
by the American authorities.

16:14.640 --> 16:19.520
At a substantial price, but he's free.

16:19.603 --> 16:23.607
And I'm told he will be returning home
to continue operations.

16:23.691 --> 16:27.778
That is good news. But coming south, you say?

16:27.861 --> 16:28.862
<i>That's correct.</i>

16:28.946 --> 16:33.075
Forfeiting bail is the only way
to assure he remains out of prison.

16:33.158 --> 16:35.369
<i>Well, then. All will be returning to normal.</i>

16:35.452 --> 16:40.040
<i>And I trust your run of bad luck</i>
<i>will be behind you.</i>

16:40.124 --> 16:41.709
Bad luck?

16:41.792 --> 16:45.838
<i>The DEA. The fire. The arrest.</i>

16:47.131 --> 16:48.799
My hope is that it's over.

16:50.217 --> 16:53.971
Yes. I believe the coming weeks
will be our best yet.

16:54.054 --> 16:57.057
<i>Excellent. I'll pass on the good news.</i>

16:57.141 --> 16:58.475
[BOLSA SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:58.559 --> 17:01.270
Thank you. Enjoy your evening.

17:06.859 --> 17:09.862
I just spoke to the man
responsible for the attack.

17:11.613 --> 17:14.366
Someone we need to worry about?

17:14.450 --> 17:17.578
He was trying to protect his own business

17:17.661 --> 17:19.788
by protecting our business.

17:21.040 --> 17:23.000
If that's him trying to help...

17:23.083 --> 17:25.753
He knows nothing
of what we are trying to accomplish.

17:26.420 --> 17:29.882
Once Salamanca is south of the border,

17:29.965 --> 17:33.719
our actions must be unimpeachable.

17:33.802 --> 17:38.390
Any reflection on me
will not be greeted with kindness.

17:39.516 --> 17:40.976
All right.

17:48.233 --> 17:49.693
Yes?

17:51.278 --> 17:53.864
There's one other thing we should discuss.

17:56.825 --> 17:59.703
Nacho Varga. He wants out.

18:00.579 --> 18:04.249
He's done everything we asked,
he held up his end.

18:04.333 --> 18:07.086
I think it's time we cut him loose.

18:07.169 --> 18:09.296
I see no reason to give up an asset.

18:09.379 --> 18:13.175
Once Salamanca's dealt with,
we have no use for Varga.

18:13.258 --> 18:15.427
He's the only guy they have
running things up here.

18:15.511 --> 18:19.723
He disappears, Salamanca operation falls apart.

18:26.355 --> 18:28.398
Varga stays.

18:28.482 --> 18:31.819
Better to control the opposition
without their knowledge.

18:34.988 --> 18:37.407
You have a gun to his father's head.

18:38.075 --> 18:39.785
That doesn't sit with me.

18:40.786 --> 18:43.413
You wanna keep Varga for the long run,

18:44.414 --> 18:47.626
I don't think fear is a great motivator.

18:50.629 --> 18:56.260
A dog who bites every owner he's had...

18:57.553 --> 19:00.389
can only disciplined with a firm hand.

19:00.472 --> 19:03.809
Or put down.

19:15.696 --> 19:18.448
He's taking care of business tonight.

19:18.532 --> 19:21.577
Tomorrow morning,
he's seeing Hector to say goodbye.

19:22.661 --> 19:25.539
Um, after that, I drive him south.
He didn't tell me where.

19:25.622 --> 19:27.624
All I know is I'm dropping him off

19:27.708 --> 19:31.295
and somebody else is taking him over the border.

19:31.378 --> 19:32.588
TYRUS [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Is that it?</i>

19:32.671 --> 19:35.257
Yeah. Hey, um...

19:37.176 --> 19:41.346
Once he's down, that's it, right? He's done?

19:43.223 --> 19:45.559
<i>Just do what you're told. Don't worry about it.</i>

20:05.245 --> 20:06.121
Hey.

20:07.122 --> 20:08.207
Hungry?

20:09.208 --> 20:14.129
You good with cereal?
Or you want me to try an omelet?

20:15.214 --> 20:18.675
Uh, cereal.
Probably the safest thing for my stomach.

20:18.759 --> 20:20.552
-Okay.
-I'll get it.

20:20.636 --> 20:22.638
No, no, no. I got it. Just...

20:22.721 --> 20:25.265
Just relax.

20:34.566 --> 20:36.735
You going in late today?

20:37.819 --> 20:41.698
Uh, I just thought I'd stay home today.

20:44.159 --> 20:45.994
Kim, I can take care of myself.

20:46.078 --> 20:50.624
Well, I already called in sick,
so you're stuck with me.

20:51.667 --> 20:52.793
[JUICER WHIRRING]

21:26.827 --> 21:29.162
Oh! Damn it!

21:30.372 --> 21:31.623
Shit.

21:31.707 --> 21:33.709
-I'm sorry.
-That's okay.

21:34.751 --> 21:36.920
I guess my stomach's just not ready for this yet.

21:39.881 --> 21:41.258
It's okay.

21:43.593 --> 21:45.679
Not a big deal.

22:04.114 --> 22:06.491
Are you sure you don't have to go in to work?

22:06.575 --> 22:09.911
Yeah, I'm sure. We both need to take it easy.

22:09.995 --> 22:11.955
How about a day without drama?

22:13.123 --> 22:15.125
That sounds real good, actually.

22:15.208 --> 22:16.752
[TV TURNS ON]

22:16.835 --> 22:18.587
HILDY:
<i>Oh, hi, Skinny.</i>

22:18.670 --> 22:20.964
-<i>Hello, Ruth.</i>
RUTH: <i>Well, Maisie's here.</i>

22:21.048 --> 22:23.342
HILDY: <i>How are you?</i>
<i>Tell me, is the lord of the universe in?</i>

22:23.425 --> 22:26.595
MAISIE: <i>Yes, he's in, in a bad humor.</i>
<i>Somebody must have stolen the crown jewel.</i>

22:26.678 --> 22:29.806
<i>-Shall we announce you?</i>
HILDY: <i>Oh, no, no. I'll blow my own horn.</i>

22:29.890 --> 22:32.517
<i>Bruce, you should better wait here.</i>
<i>I'll be back in 10 minutes.</i>

22:32.601 --> 22:35.771
BRUCE: <i>Even 10 minutes is a long time</i>
<i>to be away from you.</i>

22:36.772 --> 22:38.940
HILDY:<i> What did you say?</i>
BRUCE: <i>What?</i>

22:39.941 --> 22:41.693
<i>-Well...</i>
<i>-Go on.</i>

22:43.153 --> 22:44.279
<i>Well, go ahead.</i>

22:44.362 --> 22:47.783
BRUCE: <i>Well, I just said, even 10 minutes</i>
<i>is a long time to be away from you.</i>

22:47.866 --> 22:51.995
HILDY: <i>I heard you the first time.</i>
<i>I like it, that's why I asked you to say it again.</i>

22:52.079 --> 22:55.749
<i>I can stand being spoiled. The gentleman</i>
<i>I'm going in to see did very little spoiling.</i>

22:55.832 --> 22:58.960
BRUCE: <i>I'd like to spoil him just once.</i>
<i>You sure you don't want me to go with you?</i>

22:59.044 --> 23:02.214
HILDY:<i> Oh, no. I can handle it.</i>
<i>-Well, if things get rough, remember I'm here.</i>

23:02.297 --> 23:03.548
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

23:06.635 --> 23:08.386
<i>Hi, Hildy. Welcome back.</i>

23:08.470 --> 23:11.348
Saul Goodman. Speedy justice for you.

23:13.391 --> 23:18.730
I'm sorry. No. Today-- It's impossible today.
I can't help you.

23:20.649 --> 23:22.109
Yeah, that's right.

23:26.613 --> 23:29.491
Uh, wait, what are they saying?

23:30.992 --> 23:32.202
Are you--?

23:32.285 --> 23:34.704
Just wait 45 minutes. I can be there.

23:34.788 --> 23:36.456
[WHISPERING] What? Jimmy, no.

23:36.540 --> 23:38.667
Yeah. You tell them I'm on my way.

23:39.709 --> 23:41.711
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Jimmy. Jimmy.

23:41.795 --> 23:44.047
You can barely walk. What are you doing?

23:44.131 --> 23:46.633
It's my client. He's in big trouble.

23:47.926 --> 23:51.680
They're trying to kill his plea deal
because his buddy was carrying weed.

23:51.763 --> 23:52.639
What? Okay.

23:52.722 --> 23:55.600
So get a continuance.
You don't have to do this today.

23:55.684 --> 23:57.352
No, this guy's scared out of his mind.

23:57.435 --> 24:00.313
I wouldn't feel right leaving him hanging.

24:01.606 --> 24:03.900
Jimmy, look, I know you're lying.

24:08.196 --> 24:12.492
And I know something terrible
happened in the desert.

24:15.036 --> 24:18.123
This isn't about our deal,
I'm not insisting or forcing you to tell me.

24:18.206 --> 24:19.583
I just...

24:21.585 --> 24:25.672
want you to know that I'm here for you.

24:30.177 --> 24:33.054
And you can tell me, okay?

24:34.055 --> 24:35.557
No judgments.

24:39.603 --> 24:41.229
No judgments.

24:47.110 --> 24:48.445
You're right.

24:49.863 --> 24:52.490
Something did happen out there.

24:56.494 --> 24:58.538
When I was in the desert...

25:01.583 --> 25:04.211
I had to drink my own pee.

25:05.712 --> 25:11.051
I was out of water,
and in order to survive, I had to drink pee.

25:12.177 --> 25:15.555
Well... Yeah, that's it, so...

25:16.890 --> 25:19.976
And there you go. Look...

25:21.186 --> 25:24.022
I will recover,
and we never need to mention this again.

25:24.105 --> 25:27.317
I'm gonna go get changed,
and I'm gonna get down there.

25:37.285 --> 25:38.578
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

25:45.377 --> 25:47.379
Kim. Feeling better?

25:47.462 --> 25:50.215
Oh, yeah. Just a 24-hour thing. It passed.

25:50.298 --> 25:52.842
I thought I should come in
and prep the Colorado meeting.

25:52.926 --> 25:55.971
Oh. They moved that up to this morning.
Stef handled it.

25:56.054 --> 25:58.098
There was no pushback from Boulder city council?

25:58.181 --> 26:01.977
Stef cleared up the conditional use issue.
Everything's moving forward.

26:02.060 --> 26:04.145
Wow, that's great.

26:05.438 --> 26:06.481
Great.

26:07.774 --> 26:09.401
Well, uh...

26:11.111 --> 26:11.945
Okay.

26:12.028 --> 26:15.740
You wanted to write letters
to the planning board in Broomfield.

26:15.824 --> 26:18.326
Right. Yes, that's right.

26:18.410 --> 26:20.954
I'll get started on that,
if you can just get me those names.

26:21.037 --> 26:24.374
-List is on your desk.
-Of course. Great.

26:28.712 --> 26:34.009
First letter is for Mr. Armand Bakaris,
chairman of the Planning and Zoning Commission,

26:34.092 --> 26:36.886
and let's just CC the vice chair,

26:36.970 --> 26:39.264
Elaine Perlman, while we're at it.

26:40.390 --> 26:42.350
Dear Mr. Bakaris,

26:42.434 --> 26:47.480
Mesa Verde Bank and Trust respectfully submit
the following request for your consideration.

26:47.564 --> 26:50.817
In regards to the resolution number...

26:51.818 --> 26:56.906
PZ 2004-dash-36 variance appeal

26:56.990 --> 27:02.495
to allow for a six-and-one-half foot encroachment
into the...

27:04.998 --> 27:08.001
Into the minimum required rear setback...

27:15.091 --> 27:20.221
Um, minimum required rear setback for a...

27:21.264 --> 27:23.683
drive-thru awning to allow...

27:23.767 --> 27:26.311
Strike that. To facilitate...

27:27.520 --> 27:31.733
access to the property at...

27:34.944 --> 27:36.613
841 North.

27:37.781 --> 27:42.327
So can you call his assistant and get some intel
on what he's into right now?

27:42.410 --> 27:45.622
Kim, they told me you were out sick today.

27:45.705 --> 27:49.918
Yeah. No, I, uh... Rich, you free to talk?

27:50.001 --> 27:51.211
Yeah, is everything okay?

27:51.294 --> 27:54.047
Yeah. I just need a minute.

27:54.130 --> 27:55.590
Okay.

28:00.678 --> 28:03.765
So, what's up?

28:03.848 --> 28:05.100
KIM:
I...

28:05.183 --> 28:06.643
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

28:13.274 --> 28:14.359
What?

28:14.484 --> 28:15.860
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

28:30.959 --> 28:33.461
Marcie, can you do me a favor?

28:33.545 --> 28:36.381
Copy all the pro bono files
and send the originals to my place.

28:36.464 --> 28:40.260
Also, no rush, but
box up my diplomas and photos, please.

28:40.343 --> 28:42.387
Are we moving offices?

28:42.470 --> 28:46.099
I don't want you to worry. I talked to Rich,
you'll be reassigned to another partner.

28:46.182 --> 28:47.267
Wait, reassigned?

28:47.350 --> 28:50.103
Oh, and they're gonna want these.

28:51.104 --> 28:54.107
I'm parked in my usual spot.

28:54.190 --> 28:58.486
If I left anything else in there,
just put it in the box.

29:00.613 --> 29:02.073
Thank you, Marcie.

29:03.074 --> 29:05.285
-Good luck.
-Kim...

29:29.476 --> 29:30.852
LALO [IN SPANISH]:
Look.

29:30.935 --> 29:35.106
Cops are gonna go crazy looking for me
for a few months.

29:35.190 --> 29:37.233
Maybe a year.

29:37.317 --> 29:40.320
Then the heat will die down, like it always does.

29:40.403 --> 29:41.488
Until then,

29:41.571 --> 29:46.117
Ignacio or one of the other guys,
they'll get you anything you need.

29:47.619 --> 29:49.579
Tio, come on. Don't be this way.

29:50.580 --> 29:54.375
There are still lots of moves
to make against Fring.

29:56.127 --> 30:01.007
When I'm home, I'll have Eladio's ear.

30:01.090 --> 30:06.012
I'll make sure he's sick of the Chicken Man.

30:06.095 --> 30:08.097
Then,

30:08.181 --> 30:09.808
what's Fring's...

30:10.975 --> 30:12.477
will be ours.

30:14.771 --> 30:19.025
Eleven months from now, Tuco gets out
of prison. He'll run things here.

30:20.068 --> 30:24.989
I know, I know. Tuco. He's a hothead.

30:25.073 --> 30:27.367
When he's on the stuff, he's...

30:30.245 --> 30:32.997
We'll make sure someone is on him.

30:34.666 --> 30:35.792
He'll stay clean.

30:35.875 --> 30:37.252
WOMAN:
Hi, there.

30:37.335 --> 30:40.380
We're bringing birthday cake out
for Louise, one of our residents.

30:40.463 --> 30:43.842
Everyone's going to sing.
Hector really doesn't like to miss these.

30:43.925 --> 30:47.762
[IN ENGLISH]
Yeah. Could you give us a minute, please?

30:59.566 --> 31:01.901
[IN SPANISH]
Family is everything.

31:15.832 --> 31:17.417
Okay, guys.

31:19.919 --> 31:24.007
ALL:
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

31:24.090 --> 31:27.760
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

31:27.844 --> 31:32.682
♪ Happy birthday dear Louise ♪

31:32.765 --> 31:36.686
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪♪

31:36.769 --> 31:37.937
[ALL APPLAUDING]

31:59.959 --> 32:01.210
Where to?

32:02.211 --> 32:04.088
Go. The border.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.135
[ENGINE STARTS]

32:26.152 --> 32:27.487
[ENGINE STARTS]

32:32.158 --> 32:36.371
Hey, that was something. What happened in there?

32:36.454 --> 32:38.915
Hey, look, don't feel bad. You can't win them all.

32:38.998 --> 32:42.335
But that one? Sheesh, I thought for sure
I was gonna lose.

32:42.418 --> 32:44.963
There wasn't a chance in hell
I was supposed to win that one.

32:45.046 --> 32:46.756
But there you were.

32:46.839 --> 32:49.467
Snatching defeat from the jaws of victory.

32:50.468 --> 32:53.221
Ball in your hand, at the goal line,

32:53.304 --> 32:54.889
fumble!

32:54.973 --> 32:58.601
Law students are gonna review
the "Goodman Debacle" as a teachable moment.

32:58.685 --> 32:59.936
So at least there's that.

33:00.937 --> 33:03.606
And think of all the kids you'll help learn
what not to do

33:03.690 --> 33:05.650
when faced with underwhelming odds.

33:05.733 --> 33:07.193
So embarrassing.

33:07.276 --> 33:10.113
You'll probably have to change your name. Again.

33:19.872 --> 33:24.168
Hey, just so you know,
I don't think any less of you.

33:24.252 --> 33:27.630
You're still a lawyer.

33:38.307 --> 33:39.892
[CAR APPROACHING]

34:03.082 --> 34:06.002
You can start talking any time.

34:07.295 --> 34:11.716
You said this goes away.
So, what's the time frame on that?

34:15.720 --> 34:18.556
It's different for different people, I suppose.

34:19.640 --> 34:23.519
For me. When will this be over for me?

34:26.064 --> 34:28.608
Well, here's what's gonna happen.

34:28.691 --> 34:30.234
One day...

34:30.318 --> 34:32.653
One day, you're gonna wake up,

34:32.737 --> 34:36.824
eat your breakfast, brush your teeth,
go about your business.

34:38.701 --> 34:41.037
And sooner or later,

34:41.120 --> 34:43.706
you're gonna realize

34:43.790 --> 34:45.541
you haven't thought about it.

34:46.709 --> 34:48.169
None of it.

34:51.089 --> 34:53.341
And that's the moment

34:53.424 --> 34:55.384
you realize you can forget.

34:56.385 --> 35:00.348
When you know that's possible, it all gets easier.

35:00.431 --> 35:02.725
But what about you? Like...

35:02.809 --> 35:04.977
What happened out there doesn't bother you?

35:05.978 --> 35:10.191
Them wanting to steal the 7 million
didn't work for me.

35:10.274 --> 35:13.486
Not to mention, they wanted to shoot you
in the head.

35:13.569 --> 35:17.156
It was them or it was us. Cut and dried.

35:18.616 --> 35:20.701
They were in the game.

35:25.498 --> 35:27.125
What about Fred?

35:28.209 --> 35:29.502
From Travel Wire.

35:30.545 --> 35:32.130
Was he in the game?

35:33.881 --> 35:35.591
No.

35:36.884 --> 35:39.428
There was a lot wrong with what happened there.

35:39.512 --> 35:40.805
Yeah. Lalo.

35:41.806 --> 35:45.935
Lalo killed that guy. And for what?

35:46.018 --> 35:49.105
He killed that guy, and we're helping him.

35:53.025 --> 35:55.528
All this shit, just to...

35:56.571 --> 36:00.074
So he can get out of jail and just get away?

36:01.159 --> 36:03.327
It's not the end of the story.

36:05.329 --> 36:06.831
Wait a minute. What does that mean?

36:06.914 --> 36:10.334
Uh, "not the end of the story."
What are you saying?

36:10.418 --> 36:14.172
Are you saying what I think you're saying?
Something gonna happen to Lalo?

36:14.255 --> 36:16.424
I didn't say that.

36:16.507 --> 36:20.720
Oh, Jesus. What have I gotten myself
involved with here?

36:20.803 --> 36:24.974
-Look, just tell me, what are you saying--
-Look.

36:26.017 --> 36:29.145
We all make our choices.

36:29.228 --> 36:32.940
Now those choices, they put us on a road.

36:33.024 --> 36:37.695
Sometimes those choices seem small,
but they put you on the road.

36:37.778 --> 36:40.531
You think about getting off.

36:41.991 --> 36:44.410
But eventually, you're back on it.

36:45.411 --> 36:47.538
And the road we're on led us out to the desert,

36:47.622 --> 36:49.332
and everything that happened there,

36:49.415 --> 36:53.586
and straight back to where we are right now.

36:54.795 --> 36:56.464
And nothing...

36:57.757 --> 37:00.843
Nothing can be done about that.

37:02.470 --> 37:04.972
Do you understand that?

37:09.560 --> 37:11.812
I can't believe...

37:13.231 --> 37:17.318
I can't believe there's, like,
over a billion people on this planet,

37:17.401 --> 37:21.030
and the only person
I have to talk about this to is you.

38:48.617 --> 38:49.994
You want me to wait?

38:50.995 --> 38:52.371
Nah.

38:52.455 --> 38:53.914
They'll be here.

38:53.998 --> 38:56.083
Really. Go.

38:58.461 --> 38:59.378
You sure?

38:59.462 --> 39:01.339
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

39:01.422 --> 39:02.757
Look, I'll be in touch, man.

39:02.840 --> 39:05.259
Hey, that fire you did at Fring's...

39:06.552 --> 39:08.429
That was good work, man.

39:08.512 --> 39:09.597
We're gonna do more.

39:09.680 --> 39:10.723
[IN SPANISH]
You'll see.

39:13.976 --> 39:15.144
Sounds good.

39:21.817 --> 39:23.194
[♪♪♪]

39:38.626 --> 39:41.962
Take me back up the road. Slow.

39:46.092 --> 39:47.093
What for?

39:47.176 --> 39:50.262
Just do it. Six or seven miles back.

40:05.319 --> 40:06.779
NACHO:
What are we looking for?

40:07.863 --> 40:10.491
The lawyer said his car broke down.

40:12.326 --> 40:16.163
Six miles from the pick-up. Where is it?

40:21.544 --> 40:24.255
Whoa, whoa, whoa, let me out here. Let me out.

41:40.247 --> 41:41.332
Come.

41:41.415 --> 41:43.459
Back to Albuquerque.

41:47.546 --> 41:49.173
What about Marco and Leonel?

41:49.256 --> 41:52.551
What about them? I'll get them a message.
Let's go.

42:38.347 --> 42:39.265
Jimmy?

42:42.142 --> 42:43.060
You okay?

42:47.731 --> 42:49.650
Yeah, what time is it?

42:49.733 --> 42:52.152
It's 6:30.

42:53.779 --> 42:55.823
Oh, sorry. You wanna go back to sleep?

42:55.906 --> 42:58.993
No. I'm up.

43:01.829 --> 43:05.291
You can still go to a doctor, you know?
No harm in getting checked out.

43:06.375 --> 43:08.335
I'm fine.

43:08.419 --> 43:11.839
I think I just need food.

43:11.922 --> 43:15.092
I haven't eaten since, uh...

43:15.175 --> 43:18.387
well, really, before everything.

43:18.470 --> 43:19.888
Okay.

43:19.972 --> 43:23.475
Maybe go easy. Just some soup at first.

43:23.559 --> 43:25.686
I'm okay, Kim. Really.

43:26.729 --> 43:27.563
I know.

43:28.897 --> 43:30.149
Good.

43:30.232 --> 43:31.734
Good.

43:33.277 --> 43:35.070
What about you? You seem...

43:36.280 --> 43:38.490
worried, maybe?

43:39.491 --> 43:41.910
No. No, no. It's just...

43:42.911 --> 43:45.414
I have news, but it can wait.

43:45.497 --> 43:47.791
-Let's get some food in you first.
-What news?

43:47.875 --> 43:51.629
-What kind of news?
-Nothing bad.

43:53.005 --> 43:56.467
So that means it's good news?

43:58.344 --> 44:00.054
Yeah. I think so.

44:01.055 --> 44:02.890
Great. Let me hear it.

44:07.811 --> 44:10.564
I, uh...

44:10.648 --> 44:13.567
quit Schweikart and Cokely.

44:15.402 --> 44:17.446
And I gave up Mesa Verde.

44:21.283 --> 44:23.410
How about we get some food together?

44:24.912 --> 44:25.746
Wait.

44:27.539 --> 44:30.209
What happened? Did somebody
say something about what we did?

44:30.292 --> 44:31.377
-No.
-What, was it Rich?

44:31.460 --> 44:35.673
Nobody said anything. It just, it felt right.

44:35.756 --> 44:37.633
"It felt right." What? How?

44:37.716 --> 44:38.717
I...

44:38.801 --> 44:44.682
I just-- I keep pushing Mesa Verde away
to do my pro bono work, and then...

44:45.683 --> 44:46.975
when you were gone,

44:47.059 --> 44:50.437
I didn't know what happened. I mean, I...

44:50.521 --> 44:54.066
I thought you were dead. So...

44:55.150 --> 44:58.529
That was, um... All of it helped me.

44:58.612 --> 45:01.240
To see what's important and what isn't.

45:01.323 --> 45:03.367
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

45:03.450 --> 45:07.663
So you're just gonna throw it all away?
I mean, you busted your ass for all of it.

45:07.746 --> 45:10.958
I'm not throwing it away. I did S&amp;C.

45:11.041 --> 45:14.336
I did Mesa Verde. I achieved that.

45:14.420 --> 45:18.507
I have that experience,
but it doesn't make me happy.

45:19.675 --> 45:22.302
Look, it's been a rough couple of days.

45:22.386 --> 45:25.222
So why don't you just hold off
on a final decision?

45:25.305 --> 45:27.349
Call Rich, tell him you're thinking it over.

45:27.433 --> 45:30.477
I already talked to Rich. And I called Paige.

45:30.561 --> 45:34.189
We had a nice, very long conversation. It's done.

45:34.273 --> 45:37.025
Then I spent the afternoon
in the courthouse with pro bono clients

45:37.109 --> 45:39.111
without Mesa Verde hanging over my head.

45:39.194 --> 45:41.405
Best afternoon I've had in a long time.

45:41.488 --> 45:43.198
All right, pro bono is wonderful.

45:43.282 --> 45:46.410
It is, but pro bono means no money.

45:46.493 --> 45:48.162
So what's the plan here?

45:49.246 --> 45:51.790
I don't know. But I'll figure it out.

45:51.874 --> 45:56.044
Okay. Leaving Schweikart, I get that.
It's a bunch of stuffed shirts.

45:56.128 --> 45:58.046
But Mesa Verde?

45:58.130 --> 46:02.134
That's like leaving the Yankees
to play amateur ring toss.

46:02.217 --> 46:06.972
No, it's not. I'm leaving something
that makes zero difference in the world

46:07.055 --> 46:09.475
to help people who are actually in need.

46:10.767 --> 46:12.769
This is a bad idea.

46:12.853 --> 46:14.271
What?

46:14.354 --> 46:17.065
Look. We all make choices, right?

46:17.149 --> 46:19.818
And those choices, they put us on a road.

46:19.902 --> 46:22.696
And the road has good choices,
and it has bad choices.

46:22.779 --> 46:25.991
This is a bad choice road.

46:27.201 --> 46:29.036
-What are you even talking about?
-I'm--

46:29.119 --> 46:30.037
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

46:30.120 --> 46:32.748
Saying that bad choices lead to bad roads

46:32.831 --> 46:35.042
that lead to bad places.

46:36.460 --> 46:40.756
When you decided to be Saul Goodman,
I didn't get it.

46:40.839 --> 46:42.508
Still don't, really.

46:42.591 --> 46:44.635
But I stood by your decision.

46:44.718 --> 46:47.095
And I'm not changing my identity,
I'm just leaving a job.

46:47.179 --> 46:49.181
What I did was completely different.

46:49.264 --> 46:51.934
-How?
-Because I was leaving failure for success.

46:52.017 --> 46:55.521
It's not different.
You believed it was right for you.

46:55.604 --> 46:58.398
Give me the courtesy of believing
this is right for me.

46:58.482 --> 47:01.818
And I am giving you a reality check.
This is too far, too fast.

47:01.902 --> 47:06.573
And I'm giving you a reality check.
This is really none of your damn business.

47:08.033 --> 47:09.701
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

47:11.995 --> 47:13.247
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

47:16.708 --> 47:18.377
-Yeah?
MIKE [OVER PHONE]: <i>Listen to me.</i>

47:18.460 --> 47:21.672
<i>Put your phone down. Leave it on, so I can hear.</i>

47:21.755 --> 47:23.590
So you can hear-- Hear what?

47:23.674 --> 47:26.176
Do what I said right now.

47:26.260 --> 47:28.929
Put it down somewhere it can't be seen.

47:32.641 --> 47:33.976
Jimmy.

47:48.490 --> 47:49.783
Hey, guys.

47:50.867 --> 47:52.202
Can I come in?

47:54.705 --> 47:55.872
SAUL:
Lalo.

47:56.873 --> 47:58.875
Thought you'd be down south.

47:58.959 --> 48:00.460
Enjoying your freedom.

48:00.544 --> 48:02.546
Yeah, well...

48:03.547 --> 48:05.507
Had some business to attend to.

48:06.883 --> 48:08.343
Told you he'd be back.

48:09.344 --> 48:12.139
Nice. I like it.

48:13.557 --> 48:17.519
Hey, look, you want a drink?
We got some beer in the fridge.

48:17.603 --> 48:19.187
Unless you're not staying that...

48:21.273 --> 48:23.483
You shouldn't-- I'm sorry. Um...

48:24.693 --> 48:29.781
Sorry, you shouldn't do that. It upsets the fish.

48:47.591 --> 48:50.052
Look, you wanna talk, we can talk.

48:50.135 --> 48:52.387
But Kim's just stepping out, so...

48:52.471 --> 48:54.931
Nah. She can stay.

48:55.974 --> 49:00.187
I mean, she's part of the legal team, right?

49:02.147 --> 49:05.275
Hey, relax, sit down. We're just gonna talk.

49:06.360 --> 49:09.279
Come on. Sit.

49:12.282 --> 49:13.617
Okay.

49:22.084 --> 49:23.335
So...

49:25.462 --> 49:26.963
Tell me what happened.

49:28.507 --> 49:29.925
What happened?

49:30.008 --> 49:33.261
Yeah, when you picked up the money.

49:33.345 --> 49:36.890
Just walk me through it.

49:39.267 --> 49:41.144
What I told you already?

49:42.521 --> 49:43.522
Yes.

49:47.192 --> 49:50.320
Fine. I picked up the money from your cousins.

49:50.404 --> 49:53.448
It was right where you told me it would be.

49:53.532 --> 49:57.077
Driving back, my car crapped out.

49:57.160 --> 50:01.164
It was about six or seven miles
from the pick-up site.

50:01.248 --> 50:03.291
There's no phone service.

50:03.375 --> 50:05.669
So I walked north.

50:05.752 --> 50:07.671
Through the desert all night.

50:07.754 --> 50:09.589
Well, I slept a little.

50:09.673 --> 50:14.052
But then in the morning, I walked again,
until I made it to a truck stop.

50:14.136 --> 50:16.388
I went into the bathroom and cleaned up.

50:16.471 --> 50:20.726
I bought some clothes, and I called a cab.

50:20.809 --> 50:24.187
And delivered the money,
took them a couple of hours to count it.

50:25.188 --> 50:28.442
Usual rigmarole, and then I saw you.

50:37.200 --> 50:38.744
Tell me again.

50:40.370 --> 50:41.371
What?

50:42.414 --> 50:45.792
Tell me again.

50:45.876 --> 50:46.835
[♪♪♪]

50:57.679 --> 51:03.977
I picked up the money
from those two, uh, fine gentlemen.

51:04.978 --> 51:09.065
My car broke down after about just 10 minutes.

51:09.149 --> 51:11.067
There's no phone service.

51:11.151 --> 51:15.697
And I was afraid to hitchhike
because of how much money was.

51:16.698 --> 51:19.951
And I ran out of water.

51:20.035 --> 51:22.746
So I had to drink my own pee.

51:22.829 --> 51:24.039
[GRUNTS]

51:24.122 --> 51:27.709
A lot of it. So you wanted details, there you go.

51:27.793 --> 51:31.463
And then I finally made it to a truck stop.

51:31.546 --> 51:34.341
I called a cab. Then I waited.

51:34.424 --> 51:37.177
And then he took me directly to the courthouse.

51:37.260 --> 51:38.762
I paid your bail and I got you out.

51:38.845 --> 51:42.265
I'm not sure what you're looking for here, but...

51:43.266 --> 51:44.893
there you go.

51:48.605 --> 51:50.482
I just wanna hear the story.

51:53.276 --> 51:56.738
Lalo, this is exactly what he told me,
so if you could just--

51:56.822 --> 51:58.073
Shh.

52:01.243 --> 52:03.537
I just like to hear the story.

52:04.746 --> 52:05.789
I mean...

52:07.874 --> 52:10.585
I paid a lot of money for that story,

52:10.669 --> 52:13.255
so I think I can hear it as much as I want.

52:23.431 --> 52:24.850
So...

52:27.102 --> 52:28.603
tell me again.

52:33.650 --> 52:37.028
I picked up two big bags of money.

52:37.112 --> 52:39.531
Seven million dollars.

52:40.532 --> 52:43.785
<i>Two heavy, heavy bags that you paid me to get.</i>

52:45.245 --> 52:48.373
<i>I put them in the trunk of my car.</i>

52:48.456 --> 52:52.043
<i>And about 10 minutes later,</i>

52:52.127 --> 52:54.379
my car's engine went.

52:54.462 --> 52:58.967
Uh, I tried to fix it but it was overheated
or something.

52:59.050 --> 53:04.139
<i>So I walked north through the desert.</i>
<i>I walked and I walked and I walked,</i>

53:04.222 --> 53:07.058
with those heavy, heavy bags.

53:08.059 --> 53:12.814
I walked and I walked and I walked,
and I finally made it to a truck stop.

53:12.898 --> 53:14.566
And I went right to the bathroom,

53:14.649 --> 53:17.068
and I stuck my head under the faucet,

53:17.152 --> 53:19.905
and I bought a giant pack of energy drinks,

53:19.988 --> 53:22.824
and I called a taxi, and I waited.

53:24.993 --> 53:27.370
I don't know what the problem is, but...

53:28.496 --> 53:30.874
can she leave here?

53:30.957 --> 53:32.792
She doesn't need to be here.

53:32.876 --> 53:35.921
She had nothing to do with it. It was me.

53:36.004 --> 53:37.547
It was all me.

53:38.548 --> 53:41.176
-It was all you, huh?
-Yeah.

53:45.347 --> 53:47.307
What'd you do, Saul? Hmm?

53:48.391 --> 53:50.226
Whatever you think I did.

53:51.603 --> 53:54.940
-I don't really know. I just--
-I saw your car.

53:57.484 --> 54:00.695
-Okay.
-You push it in a ditch?

54:00.779 --> 54:02.530
I what?

54:02.614 --> 54:05.283
Did you push it in a ditch?

54:07.077 --> 54:09.371
-I don't think so.
-You don't think so?

54:09.454 --> 54:12.290
Well, I mean, you either did or you didn't.

54:12.374 --> 54:15.460
So which one is it?

54:18.546 --> 54:21.132
I don't know what you want.
Do you want the money back?

54:21.216 --> 54:23.927
Because it's in a bag in the other room.
You can take it.

54:24.010 --> 54:26.346
I just want what happened.

54:26.429 --> 54:29.099
-I told you what happened.
-Did you?

54:31.017 --> 54:32.644
Look, okay--

54:32.727 --> 54:34.896
Are you-- Are you kidding me with this?

54:34.980 --> 54:37.524
-Kim...
-Do you know what he did for you?

54:37.607 --> 54:40.026
Seven million dollars of your money.

54:40.110 --> 54:44.239
He hauled it across a goddamn desert
without one penny missing.

54:44.322 --> 54:46.658
And he got you out of jail for a murder that,

54:46.741 --> 54:48.994
let's face it, you're definitely guilty of.

54:49.077 --> 54:50.912
He did everything you asked.

54:50.996 --> 54:55.500
<i>And went way beyond what any other lawyer</i>
<i>would ever do.</i>

54:55.583 --> 54:58.044
So, what exactly is it that you're getting at?

54:58.128 --> 54:59.796
What do you want?

55:04.467 --> 55:06.553
I found his car in a ravine.

55:07.846 --> 55:09.139
Bullet holes on the side.

55:10.473 --> 55:14.519
So I'm just waiting to hear how that happened.

55:17.647 --> 55:18.857
Bullet holes.

55:21.401 --> 55:22.610
That's it?

55:23.987 --> 55:27.157
Uh-- Look, I don't know what it's like
where you're from.

55:27.240 --> 55:28.533
But here in New Mexico,

55:28.616 --> 55:31.369
you leave a soda can out,
someone's taking a shot at it.

55:31.453 --> 55:34.497
That-- That's what you're on about?

55:34.581 --> 55:37.167
<i>You don't think it's possible</i>
<i>a couple of yahoos with guns</i>

55:37.250 --> 55:39.919
<i>shot up a piece of junk car</i>
<i>and then rolled it down in a ditch?</i>

55:40.003 --> 55:41.421
End of story?

55:42.964 --> 55:46.259
What kind of operation are you running, anyway?

55:46.342 --> 55:47.719
Tell me.

55:47.802 --> 55:50.805
Because I think I know why you sent him
to do this job.

55:51.806 --> 55:53.391
It's obvious.

55:53.475 --> 55:56.478
You have no one else you can trust.

55:57.479 --> 55:58.646
Right?

55:58.730 --> 56:03.860
So you sent some lawyer through the desert
with your seven million bucks?

56:03.943 --> 56:08.573
That-- I-- No offense,
but you need to get your house in order.

56:09.574 --> 56:12.827
-Really?
-Yeah. Really.

56:12.911 --> 56:15.163
If you don't trust your men with your money,

56:15.246 --> 56:18.500
you have bigger problems
than if you trust Saul Goodman.

56:20.710 --> 56:23.088
And for the record, he doesn't lie.

56:23.171 --> 56:27.634
Not to me. Not to his clients.
He's telling you the truth.

56:29.344 --> 56:32.847
But next time you have a bunch of money
and no one you can trust,

56:32.931 --> 56:34.891
leave him out of it. Okay?

56:34.974 --> 56:37.060
Try a wire transfer.

56:37.143 --> 56:39.771
Try a shell company, or...

56:39.854 --> 56:41.648
You've heard of the Cayman Islands, right?

56:41.731 --> 56:44.025
Jesus, get your shit together.

56:44.109 --> 56:49.030
And stop torturing the one man
who went through hell to save your ass.

57:28.069 --> 57:31.698
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

58:07.775 --> 58:09.235
What now?

58:11.112 --> 58:12.697
Mexico.

58:16.034 --> 58:17.952
Back to the same place?

58:18.995 --> 58:22.457
Nope. Change of plans.

58:27.712 --> 58:29.839
Come on, Ignacio, go.

58:29.923 --> 58:33.218
We got a long way ahead of us.

58:34.135 --> 58:35.220
[ENGINE REVS]

58:53.321 --> 58:54.656
[♪♪♪]
